# Parallelizing your S3 Tasks

Kui has experimental support for parallelizing a subset of operations against S3 objects. 

#### ** !! This support is still experimental. Please do not use Kui's S3 parallel support against your production data. **

To take advantage of this feature, ensure you have [connected to your S3 provider](#kuiexec?command=replay%20/kui/s3/welcome.json).

props.children:
# Accessing S3 with Kui

Kui has experimental support for using standard shell commands to manipulate your S3 objects. Some of the commands also support parallel operations.

#### ** !! This support is still experimental. Please do not use Kui's S3 support against your production data. **

Kui currently supports the following S3 providers. It will attempt to discover the credentials and endpoints, and make them accessible using a given mount point:

- [minio](https://min.io/), accessible via `/s3/minio/bucket/object`
- [IBM Cloud Object Storage](https://www.ibm.com/cloud/object-storage), accessible via `/s3/ibm/bucket/object`

We are eager to add support for more S3 providers. [Let us know](https://github.com/IBM/kui/issues/new) of your requirements.

## Supported Parallel Operations

Parallel support is new, and currently only supports a few operations. The following operations will run in parallel against your S3 objects:

### gzip

For example, `gzip /s3/minio/mybucket/myobject*.txt` will spawn `N` tasks, if the glob pattern matches `N` objects.

## Connecting to your Job Scheduler

Next, ensure that you have connected to a supported Job scheduler. The supported list is limited, and now includes the following Job schedulers:

- [IBM CodeEngine](https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-getting-started)

### I am using IBM CodeEngine

To set up a connection to IBM CodeEngine, install the `ce` plugin for the `ibmcloud` CLI, and then target a project:
